This paper deals with the problem of optimal channel sensing strategy in Cognitive Radio Networks (CRN), which is a subfield of Networked Systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the analysis of probability distributions, which is a common theme in Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically focuses on the behavior of Primary Users (PU) and their idle times, which is a key aspect of Cognitive Radio (cs.CR). The paper also uses Markov Decision Process (MDP) and dynamic programming, which are common tools in Control Systems (cs.SY) and Machine Learning (cs.MA).
